      1          /**
      2           *  @file       Vwi.c
      3           *  @brief      Virtual Water Indicator (VWI) sense water inside appliance base on monitored wash motor parameters
      4           *
      5           *  @details    There are several different input parameters like motor current, power or phase shift between
      6           *              voltage and current, suitable for different motors. To one of those input parameters,
      7           *              two low pass filters are applied to calculate signal average value and variance.
      8           *              For all kind of signals, calibration is applied which “moves” average value to expected level for water.
      9           *              For some signals supply voltage and frequency compensation is applied to remove their influence
     10           *              to average value. Variance is relative measurement and it is not impacted by calibration
     11           *              and compensation. Based on average and variance water state is set. There is different water state
     12           *              calculation for MPH and for other motors. For Smart motor reverse rotation detection algorithm
     13           *              is implemented.
     14           *
     15           *
     16           *  @Copyright  Copyright 2012 - $Date: 2016/03/09 20:16:01CET $  Whirlpool Corporation.  All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL.
     17           */
